cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image-to-image translation using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for generating new data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a GAN, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of unsupervised cross-domain translation suggests the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the morphology of giraffes and birds, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper involves the generation of synthetic images, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
